{"title_page": "Tracy Duncan", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian rower}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name           = Tracy Duncan\n| full_name      = \n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| nationality    = Canadian\n| sport          = [[rowing (sport)|Rowing]]\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1971|11|12|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Winnipeg]], Manitoba, Canada\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n}}\n\n'''Tracy Duncan''' (born 12 November 1971) is a Canadian [[rowing (sport)|rower]]. She competed in the [[Rowing at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's lightweight double sculls|women's lightweight double sculls]] event at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/du/tracy-duncan-1.html |title=Tracy Duncan Olympic Results |accessdate=25 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Duncan, Tracy}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Canadian female rowers]]\n[[Category:Olympic rowers of Canada]]\n[[Category:Rowers at the 2000 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Winnipeg]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games medalists in rowing]]\n\n\n{{Canada-rowing-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Canadian rower}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name           = Tracy Duncan\n| full_name      = \n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| nationality    = Canadian\n| sport          = [[rowing (sport)|Rowing]]\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1971|11|12|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Winnipeg]], Manitoba, Canada\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n}}\n\n'''Tracy Duncan''' (born 12 November 1971) is a Canadian [[rowing (sport)|rower]]. She competed in the [[Rowing at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's lightweight double sculls|women's lightweight double sculls]] event at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"SportsRef\">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/du/tracy-duncan-1.html |title=Tracy Duncan Olympic Results |accessdate=25 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Duncan, Tracy}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Canadian female rowers]]\n[[Category:Olympic rowers of Canada]]\n[[Category:Rowers at the 2000 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Winnipeg]]\n{{Canada-rowing-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Jevansen", "label": "safe", "comment": "addedCategory:Pan American Games medalists in rowing", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tracy_Duncan"}
{"title_page": "Research lodge", "text_new": "{{mergeto|Masonic lodge|date=March 2020}}\n{{Freemasonry}}\nA '''Research lodge''' is a particular type of [[Masonic lodge]] which is devoted to Masonic research. It is a lodge, and as such has a charter from some [[Grand Lodge]].  However, it does not confer degrees, and restricts membership to Master Masons of some jurisdiction in amity with the jurisdiction that the Research Lodge is in.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.calodges.org/scrl/rush/index.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=May 15, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080511220347/http://www.calodges.org/scrl/rush/index.htm |archivedate=May 11, 2008 }}</ref>  Related to Research Lodges are Masonic research societies, which serve the same purpose but function fundamentally differently. There are research lodges in most countries where Freemasonry exists.\n\nThe oldest Research Lodge is [[Quatuor Coronati Lodge|Quatuor Coronati No. 2076]], founded in 1886 under the jurisdiction of the [[United Grand Lodge of England]].  It accepts members from all over the world through its Correspondence Circle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.quatuorcoronati.org |title=Archived copy |accessdate=May 15, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727192821/http://www.quatuorcoronati.org/ |archivedate=July 27, 2011 }}</ref>  A book of transactions called ''Ars Quatuor Coronatorum'' (which includes the papers given in the lodge) has been published every year since 1886.\n\nMost Research Lodges have some type of transactions, proceedings, or even just a newsletter that is published regularly.\n\n==United States of America==<!-- There are a lot of research lodges, so at present, I am creating a list with reflinks that will be expanded with information from the lodges' sites and elsewhere.  If there is nothing particularly noteworthy about a given research lodge, it will likely be removed from this list after further perusal. -->\n* [[California]] has five research lodges chartered under the Grand Lodge of California:\n::The Northern California Research Lodge<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ncrl.info/ |title=Northern California Research Lodge |website=Ncrl.info |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> in [[San Francisco]] was chartered in 1940.\n::The Southern California Research Lodge publishes a monthly magazine, \"Fraternal Review\" and meets quarterly at the South Pasadena Masonic Temple in Los Angeles County.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theresearchlodge.org/ |title=Home |website=Theresearchlodge.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n::The El Camino Research Lodge,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.calodges.org/ecrl/ |title=El Camino Research Lodge, San Jose, CA |website=Calodges.org |accessdate=2016-06-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305031639/http://www.calodges.org/ecrl/ |archivedate=2016-03-05 }}</ref> located in [[Palo Alto, California]]\n::The Orange County Research Lodge<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocresearchlodge.com/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=June 24, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305051640/http://ocresearchlodge.com/ |archivedate=March 5, 2016 }}</ref>\n::The Golden Compasses Research Lodge,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldencompasses.org/ |title=Golden Compasses Research Lodge - Home |website=Goldencompasses.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> based in [[Folsom, California|Folsom, Sacramento County]].\n* [[Connecticut]] is home to two research lodges:\n::The Philosophic Lodge of Research,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philosophiclodgeresearch.org/ |title=Philosophic Lodge of Research Lodge No: 400 |website=Philosophiclodgeresearch.org |date=2009-04-11 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> based in [[Cromwell, Connecticut|Cromwell]]\n::The Masonic Lodge of Research No. 401,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.masoniclodgeresearch.org/ |title=Masonic Lodge of Research Lodge No: 401 |website=Masoniclodgeresearch.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> in [[New Haven]]\n* [[Delaware]] Lodge of Research,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.masonsindelaware.org/blue/research.htm |title=Delaware Lodge of Research - Masons - A.F. & A M |website=Masonsindelaware.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> in [[Wilmington, Delaware|Wilmington]]\n* The [[District of Columbia]] is home to the David A. MacWilliams, Sr. Research and Education Lodge, F&AM - [[Prince Hall]] Affiliated. Working under the Prince Hall Jurisdiction of the District of Columbia, it is dedicated to the conduct of research and education about Freemasonry in general and [[Prince Hall Freemasonry]].<ref>[https://archive.is/20120914171856/http://www.researchlodgedc.org/] </ref>\n* The [[Florida]] Lodge of Research, No. 999<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/FLR999 |title=Florida Lodge of Research, F&AM |publisher=[[Facebook]] |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/groups/131418150265314/|title=Log into Facebook - Facebook|publisher=|accessdate=24 June 2016}}</ref> - charter issued by the Grand Lodge of Florida.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/19971007085720/http://www.glflamason.org/] </ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.halifax81.com/uploads/Chapter_45.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=June 24, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427205417/http://www.halifax81.com/uploads/Chapter_45.pdf |archivedate=April 27, 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web|url=http://galodgeofresearch.org/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=March 22, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126092314/http://www.galodgeofresearch.org/ |archivedate=January 26, 2016 }}</ref>  - As well as Research Lodge #1 of Savannah.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://savannahlor.org/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=June 24, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304103126/http://savannahlor.org/ |archivedate=March 4, 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Illinois]] is home to the Illinois Lodge of Research, charted by the Grand Lodge AF&AM of Illinois in 1976.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://illinoislodgeofresearch.org/about |title=Illinois Lodge of Research |website=illinoislodgeofresearch.org |accessdate=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Indiana]]: The Dwight L. Smith Lodge of Research (U.D.) - Indiana's only Lodge of Research.  Usually meets in Indianapolis.\n* The [[Iowa]] Research Lodge #2<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yorkrite.com/ia/lodge2/ |title=Research Lodge No.2 |website=Yorkrite.com |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* [[Kentucky]] has two research lodges: \n::The Ted Adams Lodge of Research in [[Paintsville, Kentucky|Paintsville]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Kentucky Lodge Locator|url=http://www.grandlodgeofkentucky.org/about/lodge_info.php?l=441&alpha=S-T|publisher=[[Grand Lodge of Kentucky]]|accessdate=17 January 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017073643/http://www.grandlodgeofkentucky.org/about/lodge_info.php?l=441&alpha=S-T|archivedate=17 October 2014}}</ref> \n::The William O. Ware Lodge of Research in [[Covington, Kentucky|Covington]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kentucky Lodge Locator|url=http://www.grandlodgeofkentucky.org/about/lodge_info.php?l=442&alpha=U-W|publisher=Grand Lodge of Kentucky|accessdate=17 January 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017072903/http://www.grandlodgeofkentucky.org/about/lodge_info.php?l=442&alpha=U-W|archivedate=17 October 2014}}</ref>\n* The [[Maine]] Lodge of Research - charter issued by the [[Grand Lodge of Maine]], AF&AM in 1982.\n* The [[Massachusetts]] Chapter of Research - notable in that it is chartered as a [[York Rite]] Royal Arch Chapter, and tends to focus on Chapter-specific research.  There is also the Massachusetts Lodge of Research.\n* The [[Mississippi]] Lodge of Research No. 640<ref>{{cite web|url=http://msgrandlodge.org/new/lodge-page/mississippi-lodge-of-research-no-640/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111170202/http://msgrandlodge.org/new/lodge-page/mississippi-lodge-of-research-no-640/ |archivedate=November 11, 2014 }}</ref> - charter issued by the Grand Lodge of Mississippi.\n* The [[Missouri]] Lodge of Research - charter issued by the [[Grand Lodge of Missouri]], AF&AM on September 30, 1941 under the direction of [[Harry S. Truman]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Missouri Lodge of Research|url=http://molor.org/about|publisher=Missouri Lodge of Research|accessdate=31 December 2013}}</ref>\n* The [[Nevada]] Lodge of Research #2 - Nevada Lodge of Research #2 is a Regular and Recognized masonic lodge located in Las Vegas, NV, having a charter through the Grand Lodge of NV, F&AM, which is recognized by the United Grand Lodge of England.\n* [[New Hampshire]]: Anniversary Lodge of Research #175<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.anniversarylodge.org/ |title=Anniversary Lodge of Research No. 175Free and Accepted MasonsGrand Lodge of New Hampshire - Home |website=Anniversarylodge.org |date=2016-05-07 |accessdate=2016-06-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506232637/http://www.anniversarylodge.org/ |archivedate=2016-05-06 }}</ref>\n* The [[New Jersey]] Lodge of Masonic Research and Education, No. 1786 - warrant issued by the Grand Lodge of New Jersey.\n* [[New York (state)|New York]] has three research lodges:\n::The American Lodge of Research is the oldest research lodge in the United States, having been founded in 1931. It is chartered under the [[Grand Lodge of New York]], and meets in the [[City of New York]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.americanlodgeofresearch.org/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=April 4, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101028083148/http://www.americanlodgeofresearch.org/ |archivedate=October 28, 2010 }}</ref>\n:: The Western New York Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wnylodgeofresearch.us/|title=WNY Lodge of Research|publisher=|accessdate=24 June 2016}}</ref>\n::[[Thomas Smith Webb]] Chapter of Research No. 1798, chartered under the Grand Council of New York in 2002, devotes its studies to Royal Arch Chapter related issues.<ref>{{cite web|author=Christopher Allen |url=http://sites.google.com/site/tsw1798/home/ |title=Thomas Smith Webb, RAM |website=Sites.google.com |date=2014-02-10 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* The [[Ohio]] Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ohiolodgeofresearch.com/ |title=Grand Lodge of Ohio F & AM |publisher=Ohio Lodge of Research |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* The Research Lodge of [[Oregon]] Number 198, Chartered June 16, 1932 under the Grand Lodge of Oregon. It is the Third Research Lodge Chartered in the United States, the oldest Research Lodge on the West Coast and the Second Oldest Research Lodge in America.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.masonic-oregon.com/find-a-lodge/ |title=Find a Lodge &#124; Masonic Grand Lodge of Oregon |website=Masonic-oregon.com |accessdate=2016-06-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160623014003/http://www.masonic-oregon.com/find-a-lodge/ |archivedate=2016-06-23 }}</ref>\n* The [[Pennsylvania]] Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pagrandlodge.org/programs/lodgeofresearch/index.html |title=Lodge of Research - Pennsylvania Masons |website=Pagrandlodge.org |date=2016-06-11 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* [[Rhode Island]] is home to Collegium Luminosum<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rimasons.org/joomla/rhode-island-lodges/collegivm-lvminosvm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109055851/http://www.rimasons.org/joomla/rhode-island-lodges/collegivm-lvminosvm |archivedate=November 9, 2014 }}</ref> (U.D.)\n* The [[Tennessee]] Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tnlor.org/index.php |title=Tennessee Lodge of Research &#124; In Search of 