s=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018234845/http://www.gwlodge.org/ |archivedate=October 18, 2014 }}</ref> located in [[Fredericksburg, Virginia|Fredricksburg]]\n::Virginia Research Priory No. 1823,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knightstemplar.org/gckt/va/17/1823 |title=1823 VA Research Priory |website=Knightstemplar.org |date=2014-06-04 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> The first Knights Templar Research Priory in the US. It is devoted to research about the Knights Templar.\n::Virginia Research Chapter No.1753,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.virginiaroyalarch.org/chapters.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=February 24, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150224232212/http://www.virginiaroyalarch.org/chapters.php |archivedate=February 24, 2015 }}</ref> A Royal Arch Chapter dedicated to research concerning Capitular Masonry.\n* [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]] State has two research lodges:\n::Walter F. Meyer Lodge of Research No. 281<ref>{{cite web|url=http://freemason-wa.org/walter-f-meier-lodge-no-281/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017110957/http://freemason-wa.org/walter-f-meier-lodge-no-281/ |archivedate=October 17, 2014 }}</ref>\n::Eastern Washington Lodge of Research No. 310<ref>{{cite web|url=http://freemason-wa.org/eastern-wash-no-310/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017111124/http://freemason-wa.org/eastern-wash-no-310/ |archivedate=October 17, 2014 }}</ref>\n* The Civil War Lodge of Research #1865, chartered under the Grand Lodge of Virginia.  Research is specifically on Freemasonry during the [[American Civil War]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bessel.org/cwlr/|title=Civil War Research|accessdate=24 June 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160928141313/http://bessel.org/cwlr/|archivedate=28 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Australia==\n* Discovery Lodge of Research No. 971,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discoverylodge.org/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=July 29, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110309213145/http://www.discoverylodge.org/ |archivedate=March 9, 2011 }}</ref> Chartered under the United Grand Lodge of [[New South Wales]] & [[Australian Capital Territory]] in 1968.\n* Barron Barnett Lodge of Research No. 146 Chartered under the United Grand Lodge of Antient Free & Accepted Masons of Queensland www.barronbarnett.org.au \n*The Western Australian Lodge of Research No. 277 Chartered under the Grand Lodge of Antient Free & Accepted Masons of Western Australia\n* Victorian Lodge of Research No. 218 Chartered under the United Grand Lodge of Antient Free & Accepted Masons of Victoria<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freemasonsvic.net.au/Education/FurtherMasonicStudies.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=April 10, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318194721/http://www.freemasonsvic.net.au/Education/FurtherMasonicStudies.aspx |archivedate=March 18, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lodgeofresearch.com/transactions.html |title=Transactions \u2022 218 UGLV |website=Lodgeofresearch.com |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oocities.org/athens/thebes/6779/ |title=Victorian Lodge of Research - 218 |website=Oocities.org |date=1911-10-30 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* Holden Research Circle,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oocities.org/hrcsec/ |title=Holden Research Circle |website=Oocities.org |date=2006-03-04 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> chartered under the United Grand Lodge of Antient Free & Accepted Masons of Victoria in 1945.\n\n==Canada==\n* [[British Columbia]] has two research lodges licensed by [[Grand Lodge of British Columbia and Yukon]]:\n::Vancouver Lodge of Education and Research licensed <ref>{{cite web|url=http://freemasonry.bcy.ca/lodges/vloe&r.html |title=Vancouver Lo