0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445\") [[Moscow]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://quattrocoronati.ru/ |title=\u0418\u0441\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043b\u043e\u0436\u0430 \"\u0427\u0435\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043e \u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445\" |website=Quattrocoronati.ru |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n\n==Sweden==\n*Research and Education Lodge No 6 Aurora Borealis, [[Freemasonry in Sweden#Swedish Masonic Camp|Swedish Masonic Camp]]<ref>{{cite web| title = Research and Education Lodge No 6 Aurora Borealis| publisher = Swedish Masonic Camp| url = http://www.frimurarelagret.se/en-research-lodge-6.html| accessdate = August 30, 2009| url-status = dead| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100812175801/http://www.frimurarelagret.se/en-research-lodge-6.html| archivedate = August 12, 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Singapore==\n*St. Michael Lodge No. 2933\n\n==Turkey==\n*Mimar Sinan Lodge\n\n==United Kingdom==\n*[[Quatuor Coronati Lodge]] No. 2076 \n*Veritatem Sequere Lodge No. 9615, [[Hertfordshire]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pgmherts.org/node/251 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=April 16, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727172713/http://www.pgmherts.org/node/251 |archivedate=July 27, 2011 }}</ref>\n*Temple of Athene Lodge No. 9541, [[Middlesex]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.templeofathene.com/index.php |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080123032820/http://www.templeofathene.com/index.php |url-status=dead |archive-date=2008-01-23 |title=Athene's Temple Barristers & Solicitors &#124; |publisher=Templeofathene.com |accessdate=2016-06-24 }}</ref>\n*The Anchor Lodge of Research No. 1814.  Greenock, Inverclyde, Scotland.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.galodgeofresearch.org Georgia Lodge of Research]\n*[http://www.bessel.org/resldgs.htm List of Research Lodges]\n*[http://www.mslodgeofresearch.org Mississippi Lodge of Research]\n\n\n[[Category:Freemasonry]]\n", "text_old": "{{mergeto|Masonic lodge|date=March 2020}}\n{{Freemasonry}}\nA '''Research lodge''' is a particular type of [[Masonic lodge]] which is devoted to Masonic research. It is a lodge, and as such has a charter from some [[Grand Lodge]].  However, it does not confer degrees, and restricts membership to Master Masons of some jurisdiction in amity with the jurisdiction that the Research Lodge is in.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.calodges.org/scrl/rush/index.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=May 15, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080511220347/http://www.calodges.org/scrl/rush/index.htm |archivedate=May 11, 2008 }}</ref>  Related to Research Lodges are Masonic research societies, which serve the same purpose but function fundamentally differently. There are research lodges in most countries where Freemasonry exists.\n\nThe oldest Research Lodge is [[Quatuor Coronati Lodge|Quatuor Coronati No. 2076]], founded in 1886 under the jurisdiction of the [[United Grand Lodge of England]].  It accepts members from all over the world through its Correspondence Circle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.quatuorcoronati.org |title=Archived copy |accessdate=May 15, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727192821/http://www.quatuorcoronati.org/ |archivedate=July 27, 2011 }}</ref>  A book of transactions called ''Ars Quatuor Coronatorum'' (which includes the papers given in the lodge) has been published every year since 1886.\n\nMost Research Lodges have some type of transactions, proceedings, or even just a newsletter that is published regularly.\n\n==United States of America==<!-- There are a lot of research lodges, so at present, I am creating a list with reflinks that will be expanded with information from the lodges' sites and elsewhere.  If there is nothing particularly noteworthy about a given research lodge, it will likely be removed from this list after further perusal. -->\n* [[California]] has five research lodges chartered under the Grand Lodge of California:\n::The Northern California Research Lodge<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ncrl.info/ |title=Northern California Research Lodge |website=Ncrl.info |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> in [[San Francisco]] was chartered in 1940.\n::The Southern California Research Lodge publishes a monthly magazine, \"Fraternal Review\" and meets quarterly at the South Pasadena Masonic Temple in Los Angeles County.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theresearchlodge.org/ |title=Home |website=Theresearchlodge.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n::The El Camino Research Lodge,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.calodges.org/ecrl/ |title=El Camino Research Lodge, San Jose, CA |website=Calodges.org |accessdate=2016-06-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305031639/http://www.calodges.org/ecrl/ |archivedate=2016-03-05 }}</ref> located in [[Palo Alto, California]]\n::The Orange County Research Lodge<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ocresearchlodge.com/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=June 24, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305051640/http://ocresearchlodge.com/ |archivedate=March 5, 2016 }}</ref>\n::The Golden Compasses Research Lodge,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldencompasses.org/ |title=Golden Compasses Research Lodge - Home |website=Goldencompasses.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> based in [[Folsom, California|Folsom, Sacramento County]].\n* [[Connecticut]] is home to two research lodges:\n::The Philosophic Lodge of Research,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philosophiclodgeresearch.org/ |title=Philosophic Lodge of Research Lodge No: 400 |website=Philosophiclodgeresearch.org |date=2009-04-11 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> based in [[Cromwell, Connecticut|Cromwell]]\n::The Masonic Lodge of Research No. 401,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.masoniclodgeresearch.org/ |title=Masonic Lodge of Research Lodge No: 401 |website=Masoniclodgeresearch.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> in [[New Haven]]\n* [[Delaware]] Lodge of Research,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.masonsindelaware.org/blue/research.htm |title=Delaware Lodge of Research - Masons - A.F. & A M |website=Masonsindelaware.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> in [[Wilmington, Delaware|Wilmington]]\n* The [[District of Columbia]] is home to the David A. MacWilliams, Sr. Research and Education Lodge, F&AM - [[Prince Hall]] Affiliated. Working under the Prince Hall Jurisdiction of the District of Columbia, it is dedicated to the conduct of research and education about Freemasonry in general and [[Prince Hall Freemasonry]].<ref>[https://archive.is/20120914171856/http://www.researchlodgedc.org/] </ref>\n* The [[Florida]] Lodge of Research, No. 999<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/FLR999 |title=Florida Lodge of Research, F&AM |publisher=[[Facebook]] |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/groups/131418150265314/|title=Log into Facebook - Facebook|publisher=|accessdate=24 June 2016}}</ref> - charter issued by the Grand Lodge of Florida.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/19971007085720/http://www.glflamason.org/] </ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.halifax81.com/uploads/Chapter_45.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=June 24, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140427205417/http://www.halifax81.com/uploads/Chapter_45.pdf |archivedate=April 27, 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]] Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web|url=http://galodgeofresearch.org/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=March 22, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126092314/http://www.galodgeofresearch.org/ |archivedate=January 26, 2016 }}</ref>  - As well as Research Lodge #1 of Savannah.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://savannahlor.org/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=June 24, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304103126/http://savannahlor.org/ |archivedate=March 4, 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Illinois]] is home to the Illinois Lodge of Research, charted by the Grand Lodge AF&AM of Illinois in 1976.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://illinoislodgeofresearch.org/about |title=Illinois Lodge of Research |website=illinoislodgeofresearch.org |accessdate=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Indiana]]: The Dwight L. Smith Lodge of Research (U.D.) - Indiana's only Lodge of Research.  Usually meets in Indianapolis.\n* The [[Iowa]] Research Lodge #2<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.yorkrite.com/ia/lodge2/ |title=Research Lodge No.2 |website=Yorkrite.com |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* [[Kentucky]] has two research lodges: \n::The Ted Adams Lodge of Research in [[Paintsville, Kentucky|Paintsville]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Kentucky Lodge Locator|url=http://www.grandlodgeofkentucky.org/about/lodge_info.php?l=441&alpha=S-T|publisher=[[Grand Lodge of Kentucky]]|accessdate=17 January 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017073643/http://www.grandlodgeofkentucky.org/about/lodge_info.php?l=441&alpha=S-T|archivedate=17 October 2014}}</ref> \n::The William O. Ware Lodge of Research in [[Covington, Kentucky|Covington]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kentucky Lodge Locator|url=http://www.grandlodgeofkentucky.org/about/lodge_info.php?l=442&alpha=U-W|publisher=Grand Lodge of Kentucky|accessdate=17 January 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017072903/http://www.grandlodgeofkentucky.org/about/lodge_info.php?l=442&alpha=U-W|archivedate=17 October 2014}}</ref>\n* The [[Maine]] Lodge of Research - charter issued by the [[Grand Lodge of Maine]], AF&AM in 1982.\n* The [[Massachusetts]] Chapter of Research - notable in that it is chartered as a [[York Rite]] Royal Arch Chapter, and tends to focus on Chapter-specific research.  There is also the Massachusetts Lodge of Research.\n* The [[Mississippi]] Lodge of Research No. 640<ref>{{cite web|url=http://msgrandlodge.org/new/lodge-page/mississippi-lodge-of-research-no-640/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111170202/http://msgrandlodge.org/new/lodge-page/mississippi-lodge-of-research-no-640/ |archivedate=November 11, 2014 }}</ref> - charter issued by the Grand Lodge of Mississippi.\n* The [[Missouri]] Lodge of Research - charter issued by the [[Grand Lodge of Missouri]], AF&AM on September 30, 1941 under the direction of [[Harry S. Truman]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Missouri Lodge of Research|url=http://molor.org/about|publisher=Missouri Lodge of Research|accessdate=31 December 2013}}</ref>\n* The [[Nevada]] Lodge of Research #2 - Nevada Lodge of Research #2 is a Regular and Recognized masonic lodge located in Las Vegas, NV, having a charter through the Grand Lodge of NV, F&AM, which is recognized by the United Grand Lodge of England.\n* [[New Hampshire]]: Anniversary Lodge of Research #175<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.anniversarylodge.org/ |title=Anniversary Lodge of Research No. 175Free and Accepted MasonsGrand Lodge of New Hampshire - Home |website=Anniversarylodge.org |date=2016-05-07 |accessdate=2016-06-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160506232637/http://www.anniversarylodge.org/ |archivedate=2016-05-06 }}</ref>\n* The [[New Jersey]] Lodge of Masonic Research and Education, No. 1786 - warrant issued by the Grand Lodge of New Jersey.\n* [[New York (state)|New York]] has three research lodges:\n::The American Lodge of Research is the oldest research lodge in the United States, having been founded in 1931. It is chartered under the [[Grand Lodge of New York]], and meets in the [[City of New York]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.americanlodgeofresearch.org/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=April 4, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101028083148/http://www.americanlodgeofresearch.org/ |archivedate=October 28, 2010 }}</ref>\n:: The Western New York Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wnylodgeofresearch.us/|title=WNY Lodge of Research|publisher=|accessdate=24 June 2016}}</ref>\n::[[Thomas Smith Webb]] Chapter of Research No. 1798, chartered under the Grand Council of New York in 2002, devotes its studies to Royal Arch Chapter related issues.<ref>{{cite web|author=Christopher Allen |url=http://sites.google.com/site/tsw1798/home/ |title=Thomas Smith Webb, RAM |website=Sites.google.com |date=2014-02-10 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* The [[Ohio]] Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ohiolodgeofresearch.com/ |title=Grand Lodge of Ohio F & AM |publisher=Ohio Lodge of Research |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* The Research Lodge of [[Oregon]] Number 198, Chartered June 16, 1932 under the Grand Lodge of Oregon. It is the Third Research Lodge Chartered in the United States, the oldest Research Lodge on the West Coast and the Second Oldest Research Lodge in America.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.masonic-oregon.com/find-a-lodge/ |title=Find a Lodge &#124; Masonic Grand Lodge of Oregon |website=Masonic-oregon.com |accessdate=2016-06-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160623014003/http://www.masonic-oregon.com/find-a-lodge/ |archivedate=2016-06-23 }}</ref>\n* The [[Pennsylvania]] Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pagrandlodge.org/programs/lodgeofresearch/index.html |title=Lodge of Research - Pennsylvania Masons |website=Pagrandlodge.org |date=2016-06-11 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* [[Rhode Island]] is home to Collegium Luminosum<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rimasons.org/joomla/rhode-island-lodges/collegivm-lvminosvm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109055851/http://www.rimasons.org/joomla/rhode-island-lodges/collegivm-lvminosvm |archivedate=November 9, 2014 }}</ref> (U.D.)\n* The [[Tennessee]] Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tnlor.org/index.php |title=Tennessee Lodge of Research &#124; In Search of More Light\u2026 |website=Tnlor.org |accessdate=2016-06-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150108141424/http://www.tnlor.org/index.php |archivedate=2015-01-08 }}</ref>\n* The [[Texas]] Lodge of Research<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.texaslodgeofresearch.org/|title=Texas Lodge of Research|publisher=|accessdate=24 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Vermont]] is home to one research lodge - The Edward J. Wildblood, Jr., Vermont Lodge of Research #110.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vermontlodgeofresearch.com/|title=Edward J. Wildblood Jr. : Vermont Lodge of Research #110|website=Vermontlodgeofresearch.com|accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* [[Virginia]] has eight research lodges:\n::Virginia Research Lodge No. 1777<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.researchlodge.org/SitePages/Home.aspx |title=Virginia Research Lodge No. 1777 - Home |website=Researchlodge.org |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> in Highland Springs\n::The A. Douglas Smith, Jr. Lodge of Research No. 1949<ref>{{cite web|url=http://adsmithlor1949.org/ |title=A. Douglas Smith, Jr., Lodge of Research #1949, A.F. & A.M |website=Adsmithlor1949.org |date=2016-04-30 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> which meets at the [[George Washington Masonic National Memorial]]\n::The Peyton Randolph Lodge of Research No. 1774,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lodge1774.com/portal/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141019173300/http://www.lodge1774.com/portal/ |archivedate=October 19, 2014 }}</ref> based in southeastern Virginia\n::The James Noah Hillman Lodge of Research No. 1883,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mastermason.com/jnh1883/ |title=James Noah Hillman Lodge of Research No. 1883 |website=Mastermason.com |date=2009-11-07 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> which meets in southwestern Virginia\n::The George Washington Lodge of Research No. 1732,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gwlodge.org/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018234845/http://www.gwlodge.org/ |archivedate=October 18, 2014 }}</ref> located in [[Fredericksburg, Virginia|Fredricksburg]]\n::Virginia Research Priory No. 1823,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knightstemplar.org/gckt/va/17/1823 |title=1823 VA Research Priory |website=Knightstemplar.org |date=2014-06-04 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> The first Knights Templar Research Priory in the US. It is devoted to research about the Knights Templar.\n::Virginia Research Chapter No.1753,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.virginiaroyalarch.org/chapters.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=February 24, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150224232212/http://www.virginiaroyalarch.org/chapters.php |archivedate=February 24, 2015 }}</ref> A Royal Arch Chapter dedicated to research concerning Capitular Masonry.\n* [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]] State has two research lodges:\n::Walter F. Meyer Lodge of Research No. 281<ref>{{cite web|url=http://freemason-wa.org/walter-f-meier-lodge-no-281/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017110957/http://freemason-wa.org/walter-f-meier-lodge-no-281/ |archivedate=October 17, 2014 }}</ref>\n::Eastern Washington Lodge of Research No. 310<ref>{{cite web|url=http://freemason-wa.org/eastern-wash-no-310/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017111124/http://freemason-wa.org/eastern-wash-no-310/ |archivedate=October 17, 2014 }}</ref>\n* The Civil War Lodge of Research #1865, chartered under the Grand Lodge of Virginia.  Research is specifically on Freemasonry during the [[American Civil War]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bessel.org/cwlr/|title=Civil War Research|accessdate=24 June 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160928141313/http://bessel.org/cwlr/|archivedate=28 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Australia==\n* Discovery Lodge of Research No. 971,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discoverylodge.org/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=July 29, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110309213145/http://www.discoverylodge.org/ |archivedate=March 9, 2011 }}</ref> Chartered under the United Grand Lodge of [[New South Wales]] & [[Australian Capital Territory]] in 1968.\n* Barron Barnett Lodge of Research No. 146 Chartered under the United Grand Lodge of Antient Free & Accepted Masons of Queensland www.barronbarnett.org.au \n*The Western Australian Lodge of Research No. 277 Chartered under the Grand Lodge of Antient Free & Accepted Masons of Western Australia\n* Victorian Lodge of Research No. 218 Chartered under the United Grand Lodge of Antient Free & Accepted Masons of Victoria<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freemasonsvic.net.au/Education/FurtherMasonicStudies.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=April 10, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318194721/http://www.freemasonsvic.net.au/Education/FurtherMasonicStudies.aspx |archivedate=March 18, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lodgeofresearch.com/transactions.html |title=Transactions \u2022 218 UGLV |website=Lodgeofresearch.com |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oocities.org/athens/thebes/6779/ |title=Victorian Lodge of Research - 218 |website=Oocities.org |date=1911-10-30 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n* Holden Research Circle,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oocities.org/hrcsec/ |title=Holden Research Circle |website=Oocities.org |date=2006-03-04 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref> chartered under the United Grand Lodge of Antient Free & Accepted Masons of Victoria in 1945.\n\n==Canada==\n* [[British Columbia]] has two research lodges licensed by [[Grand Lodge of British Columbia and Yukon]]:\n::Vancouver Lodge of Education and Research licensed <ref>{{cite web|url=http://freemasonry.bcy.ca/lodges/vloe&r.html |title=Vancouver Lodge of Education and Research |website=freemasonry.bcy.ca/lodges/vloe&r.html |date=2019-07-16 |accessdate=2019-07-16}}</ref>\n::Victoria Lodge of Education and Research<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mastermason.com/VLER |title=Victoria Lodge of Education and Research |website=www.mastermason.com/VLER/ |date=2019-07-16 |accessdate=2019-07-16}}</ref>\n\n==Chile==\n*Lodge of Research Pentalpha No. 119, under the auspices of [[Grand Lodge of Chile]]. \n\n==Denmark==\n*Forskningslogen Friederich M\u00fcnter, No 1 under [[Danish Order of Freemasons|Den Danske Frimurerorden]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ddfo.dk |title=Den Danske Frimurerorden |website=Ddfo.dk |date=2010-10-28 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n\n==Greece==\n*Lodge of Research Isis No. 9<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lodgeofresearch.gr/|title=Lodge of Research Isis No. 9|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=03/04/2018}}</ref>, the premier research lodge in Greece. It is chartered under the [[:el:\u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae_\u039c\u03b5\u03b3\u03ac\u03bb\u03b7_\u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03ac_\u03c4\u03b7\u03c2_\u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2|National Grand Lodge of Greece]] and meets in [[Athens]].\n*Lodge of Research Posseidonia No. 33<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nglgreece.org/site/en/Lodges/PGLPireaus/Posseidoniano33.aspx|title=National Grand Lodge of Greece - \u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae \u039c\u03b5\u03b3\u03ac\u03bb\u03b7 \u03a3\u03c4\u03bf\u03ac \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03bf\u03c2 > Lodges > PGL Pireaus > Posseidonia no. 33|date=2016-05-16|website=Nglgreece.org|accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>. It is chartered under the National Grand Lodge of Greece and meets in [[Piraeus]].\n*Lodge of Research Archimedes No. 35<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nglgreece.org/site/en/Lodges/DirectlyunderNGLoG/WesternGreece/Archimedesno35.aspx|title=Archimedes No. 35 Lodge of Research|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=03/04/2018}}</ref>. It is chartered under the National Grand Lodge of Greece and meets in [[Patras]].\n*Lodge of Research Plato No. 70<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nglgreece.org/site/en/Lodges/PGLAthens/Platono70.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=July 27, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327141619/http://www.nglgreece.org/site/en/Lodges/PGLAthens/Platono70.aspx |archivedate=March 27, 2012 }}</ref>. It is chartered under the National Grand Lodge of Greece and meets in Athens.\n\n==Ireland==\n*Lodge of Research, No. CC<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irish-freemasonry.org.uk/ |title=Masonic Lodge of Research and the History of Freemasons in Ireland |website=Irish-freemasonry.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n\n==Japan==\n*Tokyo Lodge of Research\n\n==New Zealand==\n*[[New Zealand]] is home to Hawke's Bay Research Lodge No. 305.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mastermason.com/hbresearch/ |title=Hawke's Bay Research Lodge No.305 |website=Mastermason.com |date=2014-09-30 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n*The Research Lodge of Ruapehu No.444, [http://freemasonsnz.org/ Grand Lodge of New Zealand], Palmerston North\n*Masters' & Past Masters' Lodge No. 130,  Christchurch\n* Midland District Lodge of Research Meets at Timaru\n* Research Lodge of Southland Meets at Invercargill\n* Research Lodge of Wellington Meets at Udy St, Petone\n* The Research Lodge of Otago Meets at Manor Place, Dunedin\n* The Research Lodge of the Taranaki Province Meets at Lawry St, New Plymouth\n* The Waikato Lodge of Research\n* Top of the South Research Lodge Meets at Nile St, Nelson (and others);\n* United Masters Lodge Meets at Khyber Pass Rd, Auckland,\n\n==Norway==\n*Forskningslogen Niels Treschow, chartered 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://frimurer.no/forskningslogen |title=Forskningslogen Niels Treschow |website=Frimurer.no |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n\n==Russia==\n*Research Lodge \"Quator Quoronati\" No.8 (\"\u0427\u0435\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043e \u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445\") [[Moscow]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://quattrocoronati.ru/ |title=\u0418\u0441\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043b\u043e\u0436\u0430 \"\u0427\u0435\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u043e \u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445\" |website=Quattrocoronati.ru |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>\n\n==Sweden==\n*Research and Education Lodge No 6 Aurora Borealis, [[Freemasonry in Sweden#Swedish Masonic Camp|Swedish Masonic Camp]]<ref>{{cite web| title = Research and Education Lodge No 6 Aurora Borealis| publisher = Swedish Masonic Camp| url = http://www.frimurarelagret.se/en-research-lodge-6.html| accessdate = August 30, 2009| url-status = dead| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100812175801/http://www.frimurarelagret.se/en-research-lodge-6.html| archivedate = August 12, 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Singapore==\n*St. Michael Lodge No. 2933\n\n==Turkey==\n*Mimar Sinan Lodge\n\n==United Kingdom==\n*[[Quatuor Coronati Lodge]] No. 2076 \n*Veritatem Sequere Lodge No. 9615, [[Hertfordshire]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pgmherts.org/node/251 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=April 16, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727172713/http://www.pgmherts.org/node/251 |archivedate=July 27, 2011 }}</ref>\n*Temple of Athene Lodge No. 9541, [[Middlesex]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.templeofathene.com/index.php |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080123032820/http://www.templeofathene.com/index.php |url-status=dead |archive-date=2008-01-23 |title=Athene's Temple Barristers & Solicitors &#124; |publisher=Templeofathene.com |accessdate=2016-06-24 }}</ref>\n*The Anchor Lodge of Research No. 1814.  Greenock, Inverclyde, Scotland.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.galodgeofresearch.org Georgia Lodge of Research]\n*[http://www.bessel.org/resldgs.htm Lis